{"id":14881453,"mediaExerciseId":"88fb4092-110b-40b8-9048-07e4a83a27d5","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":488,"solutions":[{"id":5981703,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's see the formula we will use to calculate the cost of equity which we denote with $CE$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nCE&=\\frac{DS \\times (1+GR)}{S}+GR\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nwhere the dividend per share $DS$ is $\\$2.80$, growth rate $GR$ is $4.5\\%$ and the stock sell $S$ is $\\$58$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let's do the calculation according to the formula\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nCE&=\\frac{DS \\times (1+GR)}{S}+GR\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.80 \\times (1+4.5\\%)}{58}+4.5\\%\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.80 \\times (1+0.045)}{58}+0.045\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.80 \\times 1.045}{58}+0.045\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{2.926}{58}+0.045\\\\[12pt]\n&=0.09544\\\\[7pt]\n&=9.544\\%\n\\end{align*}$$\n\nTherefore, the cost of equity is $\\boxed{9.544\\%}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$\\boxed{9.544\\%}$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":44,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/cc75b84031ddc91386b3c5eaeb830259/89dd20be2971f639cbf908134289d00d/lateximg_large.png","width":114},"regular":{"height":22,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/cc75b84031ddc91386b3c5eaeb830259/89dd20be2971f639cbf908134289d00d/lateximg.png","width":57}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"33f99515-2b2d-4fe0-9c1f-c928e4b96f85","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"tota